\pard\plain \fi360\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 To paint this picture a little better. Lets look at the dynamics between skiing and snowboarding. If you know anything about the history there you will know that in the beginning snowboarders were not welcome at the ski resorts alongside the skiers. Snowboarding was viewed by many as a nuisance. The snowboarders themselves being viewed as rebellious troublemakers and vagrants that were there to ruin the good time of skiers. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf4 The ski world was one of money, affluence and decorum. You dressed a certain way, acted a certain way, and if you were at the ski resort, you had some money. The snowboarding world was one of passion, exploration, and freedom, rules be damned. Snowboarding was taking heavy influence from skateboarding and the anti-establishment culture that was on the rise in that era. }}